  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Fertile women

          2. Clinical diagnosis of bacterial vaginosis with criteria on below (3 out of 4 fulfilled
             criteria)

               -  light gray adherent vaginal discharge

               -  pH &gt;4.5

               -  Presence of clue cells ≥20%

               -  Positive &quot;10% KOH whiff test&quot;

          3. Nugent Score ≥ 4

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Pregnant or breast-feeding patient or planning pregnancy

          2. Patient with candidiasis, Chlamydia trachomatis, Trichomonas vaginalis, Neisseria
             gonorrhoeae or Herpes simplex virus infection

          3. Patient who received antifungal or antimicrobial therapy (systemic or intravaginal)
             within 30 days of randomization

          4. Any condition or circumstance that would interfere with analysis of study results

          5. Patient who have a plan to treat other disease (e.g cervical carcinoma) during
             clinical study period
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
